00:39:08,088 --> 00:39:08,309
And...

486
00:39:10,592 --> 00:39:10,952
Terrible.

487
00:39:11,492 --> 00:39:12,675
What he was saying was pretty awful.

488
00:39:13,315 --> 00:39:14,217
You know, one was...

489
00:39:14,237 --> 00:39:16,840
There was a little boy who was just screaming all the time.

490
00:39:17,461 --> 00:39:21,246
And the rest of his family, six children, mother and father, had been blown to bits.

491
00:39:21,467 --> 00:39:22,329
And he was the only one left.

492
00:39:22,789 --> 00:39:26,574
And he would stand there and just scream and then go still and then scream again.

493
00:39:27,516 --> 00:39:28,137
And...

494
00:39:28,538 --> 00:39:31,827
And he was telling these things and he says, you know, you just do what you can do.

495
00:39:32,329 --> 00:39:34,614
And that's, he knows the limit of his power.

496
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:39,469
If he tries to do what he can't do, then you're in a burnout.

497
00:39:39,489 --> 00:39:43,981
So there's that sort of reflection in our lives about what we can do and can't do.

498
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:49,340
Yeah?

